.CENTER
<DECTAPE <MOUNTING <AND <DISMOUNTING
.CENTER
------- -------- --- -----------
.PARA
^MOST FREQUENTLY, THE <DECTAPES NECESSARY FOR <KL-10 OPERATIONS WILL
ALREADY BE MOUNTED ON THE <TU56 <DECTAPE TRANSPORTS.
^THE <DECTAPE ON THE LEFT (UNIT 0) WILL CONTAIN <KLDCP FOR USE BY
THE <PDP-11 FOR CONSOLE FUNCTIONS AND DIAGNOSTICS;
^THE RIGHT HAND <DECTAPE (UNIT 1) CONTAINS VARIOUS UTILITY PROGRAMS
INCLUDING <BOOTS AND <FTALOD.
.PARA
^^
DECTAPE TRANSPORT SHOULD BE TURNED OFF WHEN NOT IN USE.
\\
.PARA
^SHOULD YOU EVER NEED TO MOUNT OR DISMOUNT A <DECTAPE, THE PROCEDURE
BELOW SHOULD BE USED:
.SKIP 2
.NO FILL
.NO JUST
.CENTER
<MOUNTING
.SKIP 1
^^
        1.  MOUNT THE DECTAPE ONTO THE LEFT HAND HUB SO THE TAPE 
            FEEDS UPWARD AT THE LEFT PERIMETER OF THE REEL.
.SKIP 1
        2.  THREAD THE TAPE TO THE RIGHT, OVER THE TOP OF THE
            TAPE GUIDES AND TAPE HEAD, AND CLOCKWISE ONTO THE 
            TAKEUP REEL.
.SKIP 1
        3.  WIND SEVERAL TURNS OF TAPE CLOCKWISE ONTO THE TAKEUP
            REEL.
.SKIP 1
        4.  PRESS THE REMOTE/LOCAL SWITCH INTO THE LOCAL (BOTTOM
            PRESSED) POSITION.
.SKIP 1
        5.  ADVANCE THE TAPE ABOUT TEN TURNS ONTO THE TAKEUP REEL 
            BY DEPRESSING THE TOP END OF THE RIGHTMOST 
            ROCKER SWITCH.
.SKIP 1
        6.  PRESS THE REMOTE/LOCAL SWITCH INTO THE REMOTE (TOP
            PRESSED) POSITION.
.SKIP 1
        7.  THE WRITE ENABLE/WRITE LOCK SWITCH SHOULD BE SET TO
            WRITE LOCK BECAUSE THERE SHOULD BE NO REASON TO
            WRITE ONTO ONE OF THESE DECTAPES.
.SKIP 2
.CENTER
DISMOUNTING
.SKIP 1
        1.  SET THE REMOTE/LOCAL SWITCH TO THE LOCAL POSITION.
.SKIP 1
        2.  WIND THE TAPE COMPLETELY ONTO THE LEFT REEL BY
            PRESSING THE REWIND SWITCH (TOP END OF THE LEFT
            MOST ROCKER SWITCH) AND HOLDING IT PRESSED UNTIL
            THE TAPE HAS WOUND ONTO THE LEFT REEL.
.SKIP 1
        3.  PLACE THE REMOTE/LOCAL SWITCH TO OFF (MIDDLE
            POSITION) AND REMOVE THE TAPE.
.PAGE
.INDEX <DECTAPE <FORMATTING
.NO JUST
.CENTER;FORMATTING A DECTAPE
.CENTER;--------------------
.SKIP 1;A. TO FORMAT DECTAPE:
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;1. READ IN KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;2. CONTROL C OUT OF KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;3. AT PROMPT '>.' P YPTC.BIN _<CR>
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;4. COMES BACK TO PROMPT '>.'
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;5. MAKE SURE TAPE TO BE FORMATTED IS ON "DT0"
.INDENT 6;AND IS "WRITE-ENABLED" AND IN "REMOTE".
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;6. MAKE SURE OTHER UNIT NOT BEING USED IS OFF.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;7. ENABLE "WRITE ALL" AND "WRITE T_&M" SWITCHES.
.INDENT 6;(LOCATED BEHIND PANEL ABOVE DECTAPE UNITS)
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;8. PUSH "HALT" ON 11/40 (MINI-CONSOLE).
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;9. LOAD ADDRESS "600" INTO 11/40.
.INDENT 6;(PUSH ADDRESS SWITCHES "7_&8" UP)
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 2;10. PUSH "LOAD ADR" ON 11/40.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 2;11. PUSH "HALT" BACK UP ON 11/40.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 2;12. PUSH "START" ON 11/40 AND TAPE SHOULD START
.INDENT 6;FORMATTING.
.SKIP 1;B. TO VERIFY FORMATTED DECTAPE:
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;1. LEAVE FORMATTED TAPE ON UNIT EXACTLY AS IS.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;2. DISABLE "WRITE T_&M" SWITCH.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;3. REWIND FORMATTED TAPE PARTIALLY.
.INDENT 6;(UNIT MUST BE IN "LOCAL" TO REWIND)
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;4. AFTER REWINDING, PUT UNIT BACK IN "REMOTE".
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;5. PUSH "CONTINUE" ON 11/40 AND TAPE VERIFIES.
.FILL.JUST
.LEFT MARGIN 0
.NOTE
AFTER FORMATTING TAPE, BE SURE TO DISABLE "WRITE ALL" SWITCH AND REMOVE
ADDRESS "600" ON 11/40 BY PUSHING DOWN ADDRESS SWITCHES "7_&8".
THIS MUST BE DONE BEFORE READING IN KLDCP OR COPYING A TAPE.
.END NOTE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.LEFT MARGIN 10
.PAGE
.INDEX <DECTAPE <DUPLICATION
.CENTER;COPYING A DECTAPE
.CENTER;-----------------
.SKIP 2;A. CHECKING TO SEE IF DECTAPE IS FORMATTED:
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;1. READ IN KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;2. CONTROL C OUT OF KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;3. AT PROMPT '>.' P KLDCPU.A11 _<CR>
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;4. AT PROMPT '>.' SED _<CR>
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;5. COMES TO PROMPT '*'
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;6. MOUNT TAPE YOU ARE COPYING TO ON "DT1".
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;7. MAKE SURE "WRITE ALL" AND "WRITE T_&M" SWITCHES
.INDENT 6;ARE DISABLED AND "DT1" IS "WRITE-ENABLED".
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;8. AT PROMPT '*' DIR DT1 _<CR>
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;9. IF TAPE IS FORMATTED, "FREE FILES:56, FREE BLOCKS:
.INDENT 6;507" WILL OUTPUT. IF NOT FORMATTED, FORMAT BEFORE COPY.
.SKIP 1;B. TO COPY DECTAPE:
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;1. MOUNT TAPE TO BE COPIED ON "DT0" AND MAKE SURE
.INDENT 6;UNIT IS ON "WRITE LOCK".
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;2. AT PROMPT '*' DTCOPY _<CR>
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;3. WILL ASK YOU TO MOUNT MASTER TAPE ON "UNIT 0" AND
.INDENT 6;NEW DECTAPE ON "UNIT 1". TYPE ALTMODE WHEN READY.
.INDENT 6;(IF ABOVE PROCEDURE WAS FOLLOWED, TAPES ARE ON PROPER
.INDENT 6;UNITS)
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;4. TAPE AUTOMATICALLY VERIFIES, AND "COMPLETE" WILL
.INDENT 6;PRINT OUT IF COPY IS ALRIGHT.
.SKIP 1
.INDENT 3;5. AT PROMPT '*' DIR DT1 _<CR>
.INDENT 6;(TO OBTAIN DIRECTORY OF FILES ON TAPE)
.PAGE
.INDEX <DECTAPE <FILE <DELETING
.CENTER;DELETING FILES FROM DECTAPE
.CENTER;---------------------------
.SKIP 2
1. READ IN KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
2. CONTROL C OUT OF KLDCP.
.SKIP 1
3. AT PROMPT '>.' P KLDCPU.A11 _<CR>
.SKIP 1
4. AT PROMPT '>.' SED _<CR>
.SKIP 1
5. COMES TO PROMPT '*'
.SKIP 1
6. MOUNT TAPE YOU ARE DELETING FILES FROM ON "DT1".
.SKIP 1
7. MAKE SURE "WRITE ALL" AND "WRITE T_&M" SWITCHES
.INDENT 3;ARE DISABLED AND "DT1" IS "WRITE-ENABLED".
.SKIP 1
8. MAKE SURE OTHER UNIT NOT BEING USED IS OFF.
.FILL.JUST
.LEFT MARGIN 0
.NOTE
AFTER STEPS 1-7 ARE COMPLETED, AND ANYTIME THEREAFTER IN DELETING
AND APPENDING PROCEDURES, YOU CAN DO A "DIR DT1" AT PROMPT '*'
TO SEE WHAT FILES ARE ON TAPE BEFORE BEGINNING, OR TO CHECK IF THE
PROCEDURE IS WORKING. YOU CAN ALSO DO A "DIR DT_#:YOUR.FIL _<CR>"
TO CHECK FOR AN INDIVIDUAL FILE ON EITHER TAPE. SUBSTITUTE YOUR FILE
NAME FOR "YOUR.FIL" IN THESE PROCEDURES.
.END NOTE
.NOFILL.NOJUST
.LEFT MARGIN 10
9. AT PROMPT '*' DEL DT1:YOUR.FIL _<CR>
.INDENT 3;(THIS CAN BE REPEATED AS MANY TIMES AS NECESSARY)
.SKIP 1
10. AT PROMPT '*' DIR DT1 _<CR>
.INDENT 4;(TO OBTAIN DIRECTORY OF FILES ON TAPE)
.PAGE
.INDEX <DECTAPE <FILE <APPENDING
.CENTER;APPENDING FILES TO DECTAPE
.CENTER;--------------------------
.FILL.JUST
.LEFT MARGIN 0
