^FOR NORMAL CRASH SITUATIONS, THE <TYMCOM-KL OPERATING SYSTEM IS ABLE
TO HALT THE SYSTEM, DUMP A CORE IMAGE TO A FIXED AREA OF THE DISK,
INITIATE A <BT (BOOTS) AND RESTART.
^THESE NORMAL RECOVERY SITUATIONS ARE DESCRIBED ELSEWHERE.
^OCCASIONALLY HOWEVER, A PROBLEM ARISES WHICH DISABLES THE NORMAL
CRASH / AUTO-RESTART SEQUENCE:
^THE <KL-10 WILL APPEAR TO BE HUNG UP.
^SYMPTOMS OF THIS ABNORMAL SITUATION MAY INCLUDE:
.NO FILL
