<M.A.R.
.END NOTE
2) ^CONTACT MAINTENANCE AND WHEN THEY ARRIVE, TAKE THE APPROPRIATE
STEPS TO TURN THE SYSTEM OVER TO THEM FOR DIAGNOSTICS AND
CORRECTIVE ACTION.
^BE SURE TO ENTER A <1DOWN MESSAGE IF IT APPEARS THE SYSTEM WILL
BE UNAVAILABLE FOR MORE THAN 30 MINUTES.
.SKIP 1
3) ^IF <T/M IS NOT AVAILABLE YOU SHOULD MANUALLY CHECK CORE WITH <NEWSCN.
^THIS ANALYSIS BEGINS TO ISOLATE THE PROBLEM TO A PARTICULAR PORTION
OF MEMORY AND HELPS DETERMINE HOW 'SOLID' THE PARITY
ERROR CONDITION IS. ^REFER TO THE <ERRORS <AND <RECOVERIES SECTION
OF THIS DOCUMENT FOR DETAILS.
.PARA
^IT MAY EVENTUALLY BE NECESSARY TO RECONFIGURE
MEMORY AND DESELECT A BAD PORTION OF CORE.  ^IT IS BETTER TO RUN
WITH LESS MEMORY ONLINE THAN TO CRASH AGAIN WITH ANOTHER PARITY
ERROR IN MONITOR MODE.
^THIS PROCEDURE IS ALSO DESCRIBED IN THE <ERRORS <AND <RECOVERIES SECTION.
