.PARA
^IF THE MEMORY REPORTED TO BE ONLINE IS DIFFERENT THAN WHAT YOU EXPECT,
CHECK TO <ARM10LX TO SEE IF ANY SECTORS ARE HUNG.
^THIS WOULD BE EVIDENT BY THE CONTROL ERROR LIGHTS BEING ON.
^TO CLEAR A HUNG SECTOR PRESS THE <RESET BUTTON FOR THE AFFECTED SECTOR.
^TO CLEAR THE ENTIRE <ARM-10LX MOVE THE HANG/CONT/CLEAR
SWITCH TO THE CLEAR POSITION.
.PARA
^ON A <TYMCOM-X WITH MORE THAN ONE <ARM-10LX ONLINE, IF ANY PART OF
       THE LOWER <ARM-10 IS DESELECTED YOU WILL RECEIVE THE MESSAGE
       'HOLE IN CORE FROM ADDR1-ADDR2' WHEN YOU BRING THE
       SYSTEM UP. ^THIS MAY BE ACCEPTIBLE: JUST A REFLECTION THAT PART 
       OF PHYSICAL MEMORY BOX 0 IS OFF LINE BECAUSE IT WAS DESELETED.
       ^HOWEVER ON MANUAL CORE SCANS THE FIRST <NXM WILL OCCUR AT THE
       LOW ADDRESS OF THE MEMORY DESELECTED.
^THIS WILL NOT HINDER MONITOR OPERATION OR SYSTEM BRINGUP UNLESS THE
HOLE IN CORE OCCURS IN THE LOW <ARM-10LX IN ADDRESS SPACE NEEDED FOR
THE MONITOR.
^IN THIS SITUATION, EITHER SECTORS OR ENTIRE <LX'S CAN BE READDRESSED
USING THE SECTOR ADDRESS SWITCHES.
^THIS ADDRESS SWITCHING SHOULD BE LEFT TO <TYMSHARE <MAINTENANCE
IF AT ALL POSSIBLE.
.PARA
^IF ANY OF THE <ARM-10LX CONTROL STATUS LIGHTS ARE ON, MEMORY
MALFUNCTIONS MAY BE IN THE CONTROLLER RATHER THAN PARITY ERRORS.
^AGAIN, MAINTENANCE INTERVENTION IS NECESSARY FOR THIS.
