.PARA
^A ^TYMSHARE DEVELOPED PROGRAM CALLED <NEWSCN.CMD HAS BEEN DEVELOPED
TO SEARCH FOR HARD PARITY ERRORS IN A WAY COMPERABLE TO THE CONSOLE
CORE SCAN USED ON <KI-10 SYSTEMS.
^ONCE THE PROGRAM IS LOADED FROM <DECTAPE VIA <KLDCP, IT WILL
SCAN FOR PARITY ERRORS OR <NXM (^NON E^XISTING ^MEMORY ADDRESS -
THE HIGHEST MEMORY ADDRESS PLUS 1).
^IF <NEWSCN DOES NOT FIND A HARD PARITY ERROR, IT SIMPLY INDICATES
THAT IT'S ENCOUNTERED THE END OF MEMORY - <NXM.
^IF HOWEVER, ANY HARD MEMORY ERRORS ARE FOUND, THE PROGRAM LISTS BOTH
THE ADDRESS AND DATA WHERE THE ERROR OCCURRED.
^HERE'S HOW TO RUN THE PROGRAM:
.SKIP 1
.NO FILL
.NO JUST
^^
        'END CORE SCAN'            ;END OF MONITOR CORE SCAN.
.SKIP 1
        (CONTROL X)                ;GO INTO KLDCP
        '>.'SP                     ;STOP THE PDP-10
        '>.'DT0                    ;SELECT DECTAPE CONTAINING
                                    ;NEWSCN.CMD
        '>.'J NEWSCN               ;LOAD THE PROGAM
        'MR,SM,I INIT,CCL...ETC'   ;SETUP FOR TEST
        'I PUTSCN                  ;SCAN PAGE 0 FOR BAD PARITY
        '>, I P0ONES.CCL..ETC      ;TEST PATTERNS FOR PG. 0
        'I PUTSC2.CCL              ;LOAD SCAN INTO TESTED
        'I PUTSC3.CCL              ;PG. 0 AND SCAN ALL CORE
        'ST 1'
        '>.'
        'END OF MEMORY ENCOUNTERED AT OCTAT ADDR:NNNNNNN/NNNNNNN
         TYPE RN TO KLDCP TO SCAN AGAIN FROM 0.'
                                   ;THIS MSG. ONLY MEANS THE
                                   ;PAR. ERR WAS SOFT MEMORY HIT
.CENTER; (OR)
        'ADDRESS/DATA              ;HARD PARITY ERRORS ARE LISTED
        0002000/105105105105
        0300011/456123456123
        (ETC)
        'END OF MEMORY ENCOUNTERED AT OCTAL...ETC'
.SKIP 1
        '>.'J FASCLR               ;WHEN DONE USE THIS TO
                                   ;CLEAR CORE
.FILL .JUST
\\
.NOTE
^IF <NEWSCN OUTPUTS AN ERROR MESSAGE WHILE IT'S SCANNING
PAGE 0 FOR BAD PARITY, IT MEANS THAT THE AREA OF MEMORY WHERE <NEWSCN RUNS IS
ITSELF BAD. 
^TO GET AROUND THIS PROBLEM, FIRST TAKE THE MEMORY OUT OF INTERLEAVING
AND TRY <NEWSCN AGAIN.
^SHOULD THIS FAIL, MEMORY WILL HAVE TO BE READDRESSED TO ALLOW THE
PROGRAM TO RUN.
^FOR THIS SITUATION, IT IS RECOMMENDED YOU SEEK HELP FROM
^TYMSHARE ^MAINTENANCE OR FROM YOUR LEAD OR SUPERVISOR.
.END NOTE
