.NOTE
^WHENEVER POSSIBLE, ^TYMSHARE ^MAINTENANCE AND/OR YOUR SUPERVISOR SHOULD
DO ANY MEMORY DESELECTING.
^IF THIS IS NOT POSSIBLE, CONSULT THE <ARM-10LX CONTROL/INDICATOR PANEL
DIAGRAM ON THE PRECEDING PAGE AS YOU GO THRU THIS PROCEDURE.
.END NOTE
.INDENT 5
^IF ANY PARITY ERRORS ARE FOUND DURING THE <NEWSCN CHECK, YOU MAY
HAVE TO DESELECT THE 32^K MODULE OR 128^K SECTOR CONTAINING THE
SOLID PARITY ERROR PROBLEM.
^YOU SHOULD ATTEMPT TO DESELECT AS LITTLE
AS NECESSARY TO MAKE THE OFFENDING MEMORY OFFLINE.
^THE SMALLEST AMOUNT THAT CAN BE DESELECTED IS 32^K.
.LEFT MARGIN 10
.SKIP 1
A) ^BEFORE ANYTHING CAN BE DESELECTED ON THE <ARM-10LX,
THE INTERLEAVING SWITCH MUST BE TURNED TO THE <OFF POSITION.
^SINCE EACH SEPARATE <ARM-10LX BOX IS INTERNALLY INTERLEAVED, YOU CAN TREAT
EACH <LX AS A UNIT.
.SKIP 1
B) ^FROM CHECKING THE <NEWSCN OUTPUT AND THE PARITY ERROR MATRIX
LIGHTS ON THE <LX PANEL, YOU SHOULD HAVE A GOOD KNOWLEGE OF WHICH PART
MEMORY IS TO BE DESELECTED.
.SKIP 1
C) ^IF ALL THE PARITY ERRORS HAVE OCCURRED WITHIN A SINGLE 
MODULE, SET THE '<LAST <MODULE' SWITCHES ON THAT SECTOR SO THAT
THE BAD 32^K MODULE IS LAST (THE SWITCHES ALLOW OCTAL MODULE 0, 1, 2, 3).
^ONCE THIS IS DONE, SET THE MODULE '<ENABLE/DISABLE' SWITCH TO '<DISABLE'.
^THIS WILL DESELECT THAT 32^K.
.SKIP 1
^IF ALL THE PARITY ERRORS HAVE OCCURRED WITHIN A SINGLE 128^K SECTOR,
THE ENTIRE SECTOR CAN BE DESELECTED USING THE '<ENABLE/DISABLE' SWITCH ON
THE LOWER LEFT PORTION OF THE SECTOR PANEL.
^THERE ARE PRECAUTIONS TO FOLLOW IF THIS IS DONE ON THE 'LOW' <LX BOX SO
BE SURE TO GET ASSISTANCE FROM YOUR SUPERVISOR OR MAINTENANCE.
.SKIP 1
^IF THE PARITY ERRORS OCCURRED IN MORE THAN ONE SECTOR GET
CORRECTIVE MAINTENANCE HELP.
^A <KL-10 SHOULD NOT BE ALLOWED TO TIMESHARE WITH LESS THAN 768^K OF
MEMORY ONLINE.
^DO NOT DESELECT MORE THAN ONE SECTOR WITHOUT ^TYMSHARE ^MAINTENANCE
ASSISTANCE.
